</font><P><BR>Cabot Coriolis of Tholuxe Paells<BR><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5:12:17 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm lvl 46, just dinged Sunday, anywho, at 45 I spent A LOT of time quad kiting the cocks in OT.  Used the lvl one DD to pull them (no temp staff yet) get them rounded up, snare, then just kite away.  Found the best place to do this is around the Skyfire zone.  Many lvl 30-35 people there, some chanters (I love clarity).  The cocks where all blue to me at 45, not sure if that has changed.  Only thing to watch out for are the dragoons there.  I'm dubious so they never bother me.  I tried to quad some junk in DL, but alas, this does not work, I don't have the mana to finish them (even with a 207 int and +150mana gear).  OT is just the best for quading, but I prefer to group, so I usually stay in DL or KC.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uupyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Upyer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff