Fennin Ro</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usoloc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soloc</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>9:49:30 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">What Vulp described is exactly how they should be pulled, and will work every time. Just ensure that your levitate doesn't drop before hitting shore. Jboots are sufficiently speedy for the pull, as the only time you run the risk of injury is from bad timing while swimming(was at 200 skill when I did this from lvls 45-50).</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvabannloosecannon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vabann Loosecannon</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:17:52 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I said many are green.  Provens are blue.  They also take an extra Conflag to drop.  Since I can't quad green watchers, I don't see how anyone can drop four blue Provens with Circle of Force.<br>
<br>
I don't have Pillar of Frost.  Neither does the level 47.  Of course you can drop them with Piller of Frost,  It's not a level 34 spell d00d.<br>
<br>
Also, I said I use lightning shock to pull... meant the level 12 shock of lightning.  Use your flux staff if you've got one.<br>
<br>
At 47 you can try the dwarves in butcherblock.  Other than that I say quading isn't worth the effort at your level.  I basically stopped quading once the Sarnak Knights in Overthere started turning green.  <br>
<br>
Don't expect to outswim Bloodgills with jboots and 200 swim just because sombody else says you can.  Try it out yourself and you make the call.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usoloc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soloc</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:38:28 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The idea isn't to outswim anything, because if you stay in the water too long they will eventually catch ya. The higher your swimming skill, the faster you can swim to the surface where you can always outrun em <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucorbettcrumb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corbett Crumb</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:17:12 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Never done it myself but can't use use the Eye Of<br>
