C.C.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvabannloosecannon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vabann Loosecannon</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:09:38 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">That's my point, Soloc.  You can't outswim.<br>
<br>
What Vulp said was<br>
&quot;aggro both those bloodgills, then swim immeadiately towards the other nearest pillar, and grab to more&quot;<br>
<br>
Which means you are trying to outswim... not going to work.  Trying to swim to the next pillar will most likely get you killed.  Surface, run to the next pillar, and dive back down is the only way it works for me.<br>
<br>
But, if you can swim to the next pillar before they catch you, more power to you.  I'm just giving fair warning here.  <br>
<br>
I suppose if you are already moving toward the next pillar and you pull with the flux staff, you might have a shot at it.  Does flux staff cast on the run?  I don't have one.<br>
<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanstaafl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanstaafl</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:34:16 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Use levitate.  Levitate has a SoW like effect on your movement when you are swimming.  The actual SoW spell has no affect on your swimming speed.  This is why Leveitate was turned off for Kedge Keep.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uknolanncaelestis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knolann Caelestis</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Sorcerer</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:50:19 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quading Bloodgills... how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I did bloodgills from 43-51.<br>
<br>
Use levitate and sow/jboots. You really don't need sow I suppose, but its much more difficult and tedious to kite them once you get back on shore. AFTER you pull your 4 simply surface and run on top of the water to pull them to shore. They will follow. You should be able to see their heads bobbing at the surface, but if not just give them a flux to see where they are at underwater.<br>
<br>
To pull them dive down, target one, begin swimming to the other corner. Flux it when you get about halfway (there is a small dividing line in the roof that approximately marks this point). Target one at the other corner as you swim to it. Then swim up and over his head (if you do it right you won't aggro it), towards the surface. Flux him just before you break the surface.<br>
<br>
For awhile you will just need to flux 1 at the corner to pull both, but as you get higher they start pulling in singles. To pull all 4 simply surface after fluxing the 2, then make a half circle back to the first pillar and repeat. The half circle run on top of the water will give you enough lead time so as not to be hit. In fact, you can make it a pretty damn shallow circle.<br>
<br>
Make sure you dont get too far ahead of them while pulling to shore, or they will lose interest. If you are no longer getting flux messages you are beginning to move out of range. I used to run backwards with jboots and just keep an eye on them.<br>
<br>
